==English==

====Etymology====
From [[Daniel]] and [[Danielle]], from Hebrew '''[[דן]]''', and [[-y]].

====Pronunciation====
*[[AHD]]: dăn'i

====Hyphenation====
:Dan·ny

===Proper noun===
'''Danny'''
# A [[diminutive]] of the male [[given name]] [[Daniel]].
# A [[diminutive]] of the female [[given name]] [[Danielle]].

====Verb====
# To do a 'Danny' is to loose control of a race car; recover without any damage and go onto win the race. Named after [[w:Danny Sullivan|Danny Sullivan's]] 'spin and win' at the 1985 Indy 500.

